NNAAMMEE
     kkiissmmeett — Wireless sniffing and monitoring

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     _k_i_s_m_e_t [server-options] [----] [client-options]

     _k_i_s_m_e_t___s_e_r_v_e_r [--nnqqss] [--tt _t_i_t_l_e] [--ff _c_o_n_f_i_g_-_f_i_l_e]
     [--cc _c_a_p_t_u_r_e_-_s_o_u_r_c_e] [--CC _e_n_a_b_l_e_-_c_a_p_t_u_r_e_-_s_o_u_r_c_e_s]
     [--ll _l_o_g_-_t_y_p_e_s] [--dd _d_u_m_p_-_t_y_p_e] [--mm _m_a_x_-_p_a_c_k_e_t_s_-_p_e_r_-_f_i_l_e]
     [--gg _g_p_s_h_o_s_t_:_p_o_r_t] [--pp _l_i_s_t_e_n_-_p_o_r_t] [--aa _a_l_l_o_w_e_d_-_h_o_s_t_s]
     [--NN _s_e_r_v_e_r_-_n_a_m_e]

     _k_i_s_m_e_t___c_l_i_e_n_t [--qqrr] [--ff _c_o_n_f_i_g_-_f_i_l_e] [--ss _s_e_r_v_e_r_h_o_s_t_:_p_o_r_t]
     [--gg _g_u_i_-_t_y_p_e] [--cc _d_i_s_p_l_a_y_-_c_o_l_u_m_n_s]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     KKiissmmeett is an 802.11 layer2 wireless network detector, snif‐
     fer, and intrusion detection system.  Kismet will work with
     any wireless card which supports raw monitoring (rfmon)
     mode, and can sniff 802.11b, 802.11a, and 802.11g traffic.

     kkiissmmeett identifies networks by passively collecting packets
     and detecting standard named networks, detecting (and given
     time, decloaking) hidden networks, and inferring the pres‐
     ence of nonbeaconing networks via data traffic.
     kkiissmmeett supports logging to the wtapfile packet format
     (readable by tcpdump and ethereal) and saves detected net‐
     work information as plaintext, CSV, and XML.  kkiissmmeett is
     capable of using any GPS supported by ggppssdd and logs and
     plots network data.

     kkiissmmeett is divided into three basic programs, kkiissmmeett__sseerrvveerr
     kkiissmmeett__cclliieenntt and ggppssmmaapp

UUSSAAGGEE
     kkiissmmeett handles automatically starting kkiissmmeett__sseerrvveerr and
     kkiissmmeett__cclliieenntt..
     kkiissmmeett is installed as suid-root by default. It will drop
     privs to the user specified in kkiissmmeett..ccoonnff immediately
     after binding and configuring the capture source.

KKIISSMMEETT__SSEERRVVEERR
     kkiissmmeett__sseerrvveerr captures, dissects, and logs packets and GPS
     data.  It is capable of running in `headless' mode with no
     display.  Multiple clients (on multiple computers) can be
     connected to a single server.

     --II    Set the initial channel for a channel source
           (source:channel)

     --xx    Forcibly enable the channel hopper

     --XX    Forcibly disable the channel hopper

     --tt    Set the title used for the %t field of the logfile
           template (Default: Kismet)

     --nn    Disable all logging

     --ff    Use an alternate config file

     --cc    Override capture source lines (type,interface,name).
           Refer to kismet.conf(5) for more information. Multi‐
           ple capture source options can be specified for mul‐
           tiple sources.  All sources provided here are auto‐
           matically enabled unless an enable list is also sup‐
           plied.

     --CC    Comma-separated list to override what capture sources
           are enabled.

     --ll    Override logging types, comma separated (dump, cisco,
           weak, csv, xml, gps)

     --mm    Override maximum packets logged per file

     --qq    Override sound option and run in quiet mode

     --gg    Override GPS host:port

     --pp    Override port to listen on for clients

     --aa    Override list of client IPs or network/mask blocks
           (comma separated) allowed to connect

     --ss    Run in silent mode (no console status information)

     --NN    Override server name for this instance of Kismet

     --vv    Print version

     --hh    Help

KKIISSMMEETT__CCLLIIEENNTT
     kkiissmmeett__cclliieenntt is a ncurses and panels interface which con‐
     nects to the server and displays detected networks, statis‐
     tics, network details, etc.

     --ff    Use an alternate config file

     --uu    Use an alternate UI config file

     --qq    Override sound option and run in quiet mode

     --ss    Override server host:port

     --rr    Attempt to automatically reestablish the connection
           if the server terminates

     --gg    Override UI type (curses, panel)

     --cc    Override list of columns to display (comma separated)

     --vv    Print version

     --hh    Help

GGPPSSMMAAPP
     ggppssmmaapp reads GPS and Network XML datafiles and plots net‐
     works on downloaded maps or user-supplied images (such as
     satellite photos).

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
     kismet_drone(1), gpsmap(1), kismet.conf(5),
     kismet_ui.conf(5), kismet_drone.conf(5)

